# Vercel AI SDK & LLM Best Practices

When building AI features with Next.js and the Vercel AI SDK.

## Core Patterns

- **Server-side streaming**: Use `streamText` for chat, `streamObject` for structured JSON; prefer server over client
- **`useChat`** for client chat UIs; **`useCompletion`** for text completion; favor Server Actions where possible
- **`generateText()`** for text; **`generateObject()` / `streamObject()`** with Zod for structured output
- Use **Server Actions** for AI features; implement progressive enhancement

## Tool Calling

- Enable `strict: true` when supported for schema validation
- Include input examples to guide model structure
- Set `needsApproval: true` for sensitive tools

## Deployment (Vercel)

- Serverless functions: **10s default max duration**; LLMs may exceed. Add `export const maxDuration = 30` (up to 60 on Hobby)
- Store API keys in Vercel Environment Variables—never in client code
- Implement **rate limiting**—LLM calls are expensive; protect from abuse
- Consider Vercel Firewall for DDoS protection

## Security & Quality

- Authenticate and authorize AI endpoints like any API route
- Cache AI responses when appropriate to reduce cost
- Handle loading/error states; use `onFinish` callbacks for completion
- Validate inputs with Zod; handle schema evolution gracefully
